name: .delmsgoncmdAdministration
description: Toggles the automatic deletion of the user's successful command message to prevent chat flood. You can use it either as a server toggle, channel whitelist, or channel blacklist, as channel option has 3 settings: Enable (always do it on this channel), Disable (never do it on this channel), and Inherit (respect server setting). Use list parameter to see the current states.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .deafenAdministration
description: Deafens mentioned user or users.RequiresDeafenMembers Server Permission

name: .undeafenAdministration
description: Undeafens mentioned user or users.RequiresDeafenMembers Server Permission

name: .delvoichanlAdministration
description: Deletes a voice channel with a given name.RequiresManageChannels Server Permission

name: .creatvoichanlAdministration
description: Creates a new voice channel with a given name.RequiresManageChannels Server Permission

name: .deltxtchanlAdministration
description: Deletes a text channel with a given name.RequiresManageChannels Server Permission

name: .creatxtchanlAdministration
description: Creates a new text channel with a given name.RequiresManageChannels Server Permission

name: .settopicAdministration
description: Sets a topic on the current channel.RequiresManageChannels Server Permission

name: .setchanlnameAdministration
description: Changes the name of the current channel.RequiresManageChannels Server Permission

name: .editAdministration
description: Edits bot's message, you have to specify message ID and new text. Supports embeds.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .autoassignroleAdministration
description: Automaticaly assigns a specified role to every user who joins the server. Provide no parameters to disable.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .sqlselectAdministration
description: Executes provided sql query and returns the results. Dangerous.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .sqlexecAdministration
description: Executes provided sql command and returns the number of affected rows. Dangerous.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .deletewaifusAdministration
description: Deletes everything from WaifuUpdates, WaifuItem and WaifuInfo tables.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .deletewaifuAdministration
description: Deletes everything from WaifuUpdates, WaifuItem and WaifuInfo tables for the specified user. Also makes specified user's waifus free.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .deletecurrencyAdministration
description: Deletes everything from Currency and CurrencyTransactions.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .deleteplaylistsAdministration
description: Deletes everything from MusicPlaylists.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .deleteexpAdministration
description: deleteexpRequiresBot Owner Only

name: .deleteunusedcrnqAdministration
description: Deletes all quotes and custom reactions which are older than a week and haven't been used a single time.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .gvcAdministration
description: Toggles game voice channel feature in the voice channel you're currently in. Users who join the game voice channel will get automatically redirected to the voice channel with the name of their current game, if it exists. Can't move users to channels that the bot has no connect permission for. One per server.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .languagesetAdministration
description: Sets this server's response language. If bot's response strings have been translated to that language, bot will use that language in this server. Reset by using default as the locale name. Provide no parameters to see currently set language.

name: .langsetdefaultAdministration
description: Sets the bot's default response language. All servers which use a default locale will use this one. Setting to default will use the host's current culture. Provide no parameters to see currently set language.

name: .languageslistAdministration
description: List of languages for which translation (or part of it) exist atm.

name: .logserverAdministration
description: Enables or Disables ALL log events. If enabled, all log events will log to this channel.RequiresAdministrator Server PermissionBot Owner Only

name: .logignoreAdministration
description: Toggles whether the .logserver command ignores this channel. Useful if you have hidden admin channel and public log channel.RequiresAdministrator Server PermissionBot Owner Only

name: .logeventsAdministration
description: Shows a list of all events you can subscribe to with .logRequiresAdministrator Server PermissionBot Owner Only

name: .logAdministration
description: Toggles logging event. Disables it if it is active anywhere on the server. Enables if it isn't active. Use .logevents to see a list of all events you can subscribe to.RequiresAdministrator Server PermissionBot Owner Only

name: .setmuteroleAdministration
description: Sets a name of the role which will be assigned to people who should be muted. Default is nadeko-mute.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .muteAdministration
description: Mutes a mentioned user both from speaking and chatting. You can also specify time string for how long the user should be muted.RequiresManageRoles Server PermissionMuteMembers Server Permission

name: .unmuteAdministration
description: Unmutes a mentioned user previously muted with .mute command.RequiresManageRoles Server PermissionMuteMembers Server Permission

name: .chatmuteAdministration
description: Prevents a mentioned user from chatting in text channels.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .chatunmuteAdministration
description: Removes a mute role previously set on a mentioned user with .chatmute which prevented him from chatting in text channels.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .voicemuteAdministration
description: Prevents a mentioned user from speaking in voice channels.RequiresMuteMembers Server Permission

name: .voiceunmuteAdministration
description: Gives a previously voice-muted user a permission to speak.RequiresMuteMembers Server Permission

name: .rotateplayingAdministration
description: Toggles rotation of playing status of the dynamic strings you previously specified.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .addplayingAdministration
description: Adds a specified string to the list of playing strings to rotate. You have to pick either 'Playing', 'Watching' or 'Listening' as the first parameter. Supported placeholders: %servers%, %users%, %playing%, %queued%, %time%, %shardid%, %shardcount%, %shardguilds%.RequiresBot Owner Only
usage:
.adpl Playing with you
.adpl Watching you sleep

name: .listplayingAdministration
description: Lists all playing statuses with their corresponding number.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .removeplayingAdministration
description: Removes a playing string on a given number.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .prefixAdministration
description: Sets this server's prefix for all bot commands. Provide no parameters to see the current server prefix. Setting prefix requires Administrator server permission.

name: .defprefixAdministration
description: Sets bot's default prefix for all bot commands. Provide no parameters to see the current default prefix. This will not change this server's current prefix.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .antiraidAdministration
description: Sets an anti-raid protection on the server. Provide no parameters to disable. First parameter is number of people which will trigger the protection. Second parameter is a time interval in which that number of people needs to join in order to trigger the protection, and third parameter is punishment for those people (Kick, Ban, Mute)RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .antispamAdministration
description: Stops people from repeating same message X times in a row. Provide no parameters to disable. You can specify to either mute, kick or ban the offenders. If you're using mute, you can add a number of seconds at the end to use a timed mute. Max message count is 10.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .antispamignoreAdministration
description: Toggles whether antispam ignores current channel. Antispam must be enabled.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .antilistAdministration
description: Shows currently enabled protection features.

name: .pruneAdministration
description: .prune removes all Nadeko's messages in the last 100 messages. .prune X removes last X number of messages from the channel (up to 100). .prune @Someone removes all Someone's messages in the last 100 messages. .prune @Someone X removes last X number of 'Someone's' messages in the channel.

name: .reactionrolesAdministration
description: Specify role names and server emojis with which they're represented, the bot will then add those emojis to the previous message in the channel, and users will be able to get the roles by clicking on the emoji. You can set 'excl' as the first parameter to make them exclusive. You can have up to 5 of these enabled on one server at a time.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission
usage:
.reactionroles Gamer :SomeServerEmoji: Streamer :Other: Watcher :Other2:
.reactionroles excl Horde :Horde: Alliance :Alliance:

name: .reactionroleslistAdministration
description: Lists all ReactionRole messages on this channel and their indexes.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .reactionrolesremoveAdministration
description: Removed a ReactionRole message on the specified index.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .setroleAdministration
description: Sets a role for a given user.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .removeroleAdministration
description: Removes a role from a given user.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .renameroleAdministration
description: Renames a role. The role you are renaming must be lower than bot's highest role.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .removeallrolesAdministration
description: Removes all roles from a mentioned user.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .createroleAdministration
description: Creates a role with a given name.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .deleteroleAdministration
description: Deletes a role with a given name.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .rolehoistAdministration
description: Toggles whether this role is displayed in the sidebar or not.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .rolecolorAdministration
description: Set a role's color using its hex value. Provide no color in order to see the hex value of the color of the specified role.

name: .mentionroleAdministration
description: Mentions a role. If the role is not mentionable, bot will make it mentionable for a moment.RequiresMentionEveryone Server Permission

name: .adsarmAdministration
description: Toggles the automatic deletion of confirmations for .iam and .iamn commands.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .asarAdministration
description: Adds a role to the list of self-assignable roles. You can also specify a group. If 'Exclusive self-assignable roles' feature is enabled, users will be able to pick one role per group.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .sargnAdministration
description: Sets a self assignable role group name. Provide no name to remove.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .rsarAdministration
description: Removes a specified role from the list of self-assignable roles.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .lsarAdministration
description: Lists self-assignable roles. Shows 20 roles per page.

name: .togglexclsarAdministration
description: Toggles whether the self-assigned roles are exclusive. While enabled, users can only have one self-assignable role per group.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .rolelevelreqAdministration
description: Set a level requirement on a self-assignable role.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .iamAdministration
description: Adds a role to you that you choose. Role must be on a list of self-assignable roles.

name: .iamnotAdministration
description: Removes a specified role from you. Role must be on a list of self-assignable roles.

name: .updatescheckAdministration
description: Select which kind of updates you want to be notified of every 8 hours. You can specify 'release' to check only for new windows releases, 'commit' to be notified of new commits, or 'none' to not get notified.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .scaddAdministration
description: Adds a command to the list of commands which will be executed automatically in the current channel, in the order they were added in, by the bot when it startups up.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .autocmdaddAdministration
description: Adds a command to the list of commands which will be executed automatically every X seconds.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .sclistAdministration
description: Lists all startup commands in the order they will be executed in.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .autocmdsAdministration
description: Lists all auto commands and the intervals in which they execute.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .waitAdministration
description: Used only as a startup command. Waits a certain number of miliseconds before continuing the execution of the following startup commands.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .scrmAdministration
description: Removes a startup or auto command with the provided index.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .scclrAdministration
description: Removes all startup commands.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .fwmsgsAdministration
description: Toggles forwarding of non-command messages sent to bot's DM to the bot ownersRequiresBot Owner Only

name: .fwtoallAdministration
description: Toggles whether messages will be forwarded to all bot owners or only to the first one specified in the credentials.json fileRequiresBot Owner Only

name: .shardstatsAdministration
description: Stats for shards. Paginated with 25 shards per page.

name: .restartshardAdministration
description: Try (re)connecting a shard with a certain shardid when it dies. No one knows will it work. Keep an eye on the console for errors.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .leaveAdministration
description: Makes Nadeko leave the server. Either server name or server ID is required.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .dieAdministration
description: Shuts the bot down.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .restartAdministration
description: Restarts the bot. Might not work.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .setnameAdministration
description: Gives the bot a new name.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .setnickAdministration
description: Changes the nickname of the bot on this server. You can also target other users to change their nickname.RequiresManageNicknames Server Permission

name: .setstatusAdministration
description: Sets the bot's status. (Online/Idle/Dnd/Invisible)RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .setavatarAdministration
description: Sets a new avatar image for the NadekoBot. Parameter is a direct link to an image.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .setgameAdministration
description: Sets the bots game status to either Playing, Listening, or Watching.RequiresBot Owner Only
usage:
.setgame Playing with snakes.
.setgame Watching anime.
.setgame Listening music.

name: .setstreamAdministration
description: Sets the bots stream. First parameter is the twitch link, second parameter is stream name.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .sendAdministration
description: Sends a message to someone on a different server through the bot.  Separate server and channel/user ids with | and prefix the channel id with c: and the user id with u:.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .imagesreloadAdministration
description: Reloads images bot is using. Safe to use even when bot is being used heavily.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .botconfigreloadAdministration
description: Reloads bot configuration in case you made changes to the BotConfig table either with .sqlexec or manually in the .db file.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .greetdelAdministration
description: Sets the time it takes (in seconds) for greet messages to be auto-deleted. Set it to 0 to disable automatic deletion.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .greetAdministration
description: Toggles anouncements on the current channel when someone joins the server.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .greetmsgAdministration
description: Sets a new join announcement message which will be shown in the server's channel. Type %user% if you want to mention the new member. Using it with no message will show the current greet message. You can use embed json from https://embedbuilder.nadekobot.me/ instead of a regular text, if you want the message to be embedded.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .greetdmAdministration
description: Toggles whether the greet messages will be sent in a DM (This is separate from greet - you can have both, any or neither enabled).RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .greetdmmsgAdministration
description: Sets a new join announcement message which will be sent to the user who joined. Type %user% if you want to mention the new member. Using it with no message will show the current DM greet message. You can use embed json from https://embedbuilder.nadekobot.me instead of a regular text, if you want the message to be embedded.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .byeAdministration
description: Toggles anouncements on the current channel when someone leaves the server.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .byemsgAdministration
description: Sets a new leave announcement message. Type %user% if you want to show the name the user who left. Type %id% to show id. Using this command with no message will show the current bye message. You can use embed json from https://embedbuilder.nadekobot.me/ instead of a regular text, if you want the message to be embedded.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .byedelAdministration
description: Sets the time it takes (in seconds) for bye messages to be auto-deleted. Set it to 0 to disable automatic deletion.RequiresManageServer Server Permission

name: .slowmodeAdministration
description: Toggles slowmode. Slowmode deletes any excess messages users type over the specified limit of messages per X seconds. To enable, specify a number of messages (-m) each user can send, and an interval in seconds (-s).  Disable by specifying no parameters. Options --message-count (-m)   Number of messages user can send.--seconds (-s)   Interval in which the user can send the specified number of messages.  RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .slowmodewlAdministration
description: Ignores a role or a user from the slowmode feature.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .timezonesAdministration
description: Lists all timezones available on the system to be used with .timezone.

name: .timezoneAdministration
description: Sets this guilds timezone. This affects bot's time output in this server (logs, etc..)

name: .warnAdministration
description: Warns a user.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission

name: .warnlogAdministration
description: See a list of warnings of a certain user.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission

name: .warnlogallAdministration
description: See a list of all warnings on the server. 15 users per page.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission

name: .warnclearAdministration
description: Clears all warnings from a certain user. You can specify a number to clear a specific one.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission

name: .warnpunishAdministration
description: Sets a punishment for a certain number of warnings. You can specify a time string after 'Ban' or 'Mute' punishment to make it a temporary mute/ban. Provide no punishment to remove.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission

name: .warnpunishlistAdministration
description: Lists punishments for warnings.

name: .banAdministration
description: Bans a user by ID or name with an optional message. You can specify a time string before the user name to ban the user temporarily.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission
usage:
.b "@some Guy" Your behaviour is toxic.
.b 1d12h @b1nzy Come back when u chill

name: .unbanAdministration
description: Unbans a user with the provided user#discrim or id.RequiresBanMembers Server Permission

name: .softbanAdministration
description: Bans and then unbans a user by ID or name with an optional message.RequiresKickMembers Server PermissionManageMessages Server Permission

name: .kickAdministration
description: Kicks a mentioned user.RequiresKickMembers Server Permission

name: .masskillAdministration
description: Specify a new-line separated list of userid reason. You can use Username#discrim instead of UserId. Specified users will be banned from the current server, blacklisted from the bot, and have all of their flowers taken away.RequiresBanMembers Server PermissionBot Owner Only

name: .vcroleAdministration
description: Sets or resets a role which will be given to users who join the voice channel you're in when you run this command. Provide no role name to disable. You must be in a voice channel to run this command.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .vcrolelistAdministration
description: Shows a list of currently set voice channel roles.

name: .addcustreactCustomReactions
description: Add a custom reaction with a trigger and a response. Running this command in server requires the Administration permission. Running this command in DM is Bot Owner only and adds a new global custom reaction. Guide here: http://nadekobot.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Custom%20Reactions/

name: .editcustreactCustomReactions
description: Edits the custom reaction's response given its ID.

name: .listcustreactCustomReactions
description: Lists global or server custom reactions (20 commands per page). Running the command in DM will list global custom reactions, while running it in server will list that server's custom reactions. Specifying all parameter instead of the number will DM you a text file with a list of all custom reactions.

name: .listcustreactgCustomReactions
description: Lists global or server custom reactions (20 commands per page) grouped by trigger, and show a number of responses for each. Running the command in DM will list global custom reactions, while running it in server will list that server's custom reactions.

name: .showcustreactCustomReactions
description: Shows a custom reaction's response on a given ID.

name: .delcustreactCustomReactions
description: Deletes a custom reaction on a specific index. If ran in DM, it is bot owner only and deletes a global custom reaction. If ran in a server, it requires Administration privileges and removes server custom reaction.

name: .crcaCustomReactions
description: Toggles whether the custom reaction will trigger if the triggering message contains the keyword (instead of only starting with it).

name: .crdmCustomReactions
description: Toggles whether the response message of the custom reaction will be sent as a direct message.

name: .cradCustomReactions
description: Toggles whether the message triggering the custom reaction will be automatically deleted.

name: .crsreloadCustomReactions
description: Reloads all custom reactions on all shards. Use this if you've made changes to the database while the bot is running, or used .deleteunusedcrnqRequiresBot Owner Only

name: .crclearCustomReactions
description: Deletes all custom reactions on this server.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .economyGambling
description: Breakdown of the current state of the bot's economy. Updates every 3 minutes.

name: .timelyGambling
description: Use to claim your 'timely' currency. Bot owner has to specify the amount and the period on how often you can claim your currency.

name: .timelyresetGambling
description: Resets all user timeouts on .timely command.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .timelysetGambling
description: Sets the 'timely' currency allowance amount for users. Second parameter is period in hours, default is 24 hours.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .raffleGambling
description: Prints a name and ID of a random online user from the server, or from the online user in the specified role.

name: .raffleanyGambling
description: Prints a name and ID of a random user from the server, or from the specified role.

name: .$Gambling
description: Check how much currency a person has. (Defaults to yourself)

name: .curtrsGambling
description: Shows your currency transactions on the specified page. Bot owner can see other people's transactions too.

name: .giveGambling
description: Give someone a certain amount of currency. You can specify the reason after the mention.

name: .awardGambling
description: Awards someone a certain amount of currency. You can specify the reason after the Username. You can also specify a role name to award currency to all users in a role.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .takeGambling
description: Takes a certain amount of currency from someone.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .rollduelGambling
description: Challenge someone to a roll duel by specifying the amount and the user you wish to challenge as the parameters. To accept the challenge, just specify the name of the user who challenged you, without the amount.

name: .betrollGambling
description: Bets a certain amount of currency and rolls a dice. Rolling over 66 yields x2 of your currency, over 90 - x4 and 100 x10.

name: .leaderboardGambling
description: Displays the bot's currency leaderboard.

name: .rpsGambling
description: Play a game of Rocket-Paperclip-Scissors with Nadeko. You can bet on it. Multiplier is the same as on betflip.

name: .raceGambling
description: Starts a new animal race. Options --start-time (-s)

name: .joinraceGambling
description: Joins a new race. You can specify an amount of currency for betting (optional). You will get YourBet*(participants-1) back if you win.

name: .blackjackGambling
description: Start or join a blackjack game. You must specify the amount you're betting. Use .hit, .stand and .double commands to play. Game is played with 4 decks. Dealer hits on soft 17 and wins draws.

name: .hitGambling
description: In the blackjack game, ask the dealer for an extra card.

name: .standGambling
description: Finish your turn in the blackjack game.

name: .doubleGambling
description: In the blackjack game, double your bet in order to receive exactly one more card, and your turn ends.

name: .connect4Gambling
description: Creates or joins an existing connect4 game. 2 players are required for the game. Objective of the game is to get 4 of your pieces next to each other in a vertical, horizontal or diagonal line. You can specify a bet when you create a game and only users who bet the same amount will be able to join your game. Options --turn-timer (-t)   Turn time in seconds. It has to be between 5 and 60. Default 15.--bet (-b)   Amount you bet. Default 0.

name: .eventstartGambling
description: Starts one of the events seen on public nadeko. Events: reaction, gamestatus Options --amount (-a)   Amount of currency each user receives.--pot-size (-p)   The maximum amount of currency that can be rewarded. 0 means no limit.--duration (-d)   Number of hours the event should run for. Default 24.  RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .rafflecurGambling
description: Starts or joins a currency raffle with a specified amount. Users who join the raffle will lose the amount of currency specified and add it to the pot. After 30 seconds, random winner will be selected who will receive the whole pot. There is also a mixed mode in which the users will be able to join the game with any amount of currency, and have their chances be proportional to the amount they've bet.

name: .rollGambling
description: Rolls 0-100. If you supply a number X it rolls up to 30 normal dice. If you split 2 numbers with letter d (xdy) it will roll X dice from 1 to y. Y can be a letter 'F' if you want to roll fate dice instead of dnd.

name: .rolluoGambling
description: Rolls X normal dice (up to 30) unordered. If you split 2 numbers with letter d (xdy) it will roll X dice from 1 to y.

name: .nrollGambling
description: Rolls in a given range. If you specify just one number instead of the range, it will role from 0 to that number.

name: .drawGambling
description: Draws a card from this server's deck. You can draw up to 10 cards by supplying a number of cards to draw.

name: .drawnewGambling
description: Draws a card from the NEW deck of cards. You can draw up to 10 cards by supplying a number of cards to draw.

name: .deckshuffleGambling
description: Reshuffles all cards back into the deck.

name: .flipGambling
description: Flips coin(s) - heads or tails, and shows an image.

name: .betflipGambling
description: Bet to guess will the result be heads or tails. Guessing awards you 1.95x the currency you've bet (rounded up). Multiplier can be changed by the bot owner.

name: .shopGambling
description: Lists this server's administrators' shop. Paginated.

name: .buyGambling
description: Buys an item from the shop on a given index. If buying items, make sure that the bot can DM you.

name: .shopaddGambling
description: Adds an item to the shop by specifying type price and name. Available types are role and list. 90% of currency from each purchase will be received by the user who added the item to the shop.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .shoplistaddGambling
description: Adds an item to the list of items for sale in the shop entry given the index. You usually want to run this command in the secret channel, so that the unique items are not leaked.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .shopremGambling
description: Removes an item from the shop by its ID.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .slotstatsGambling
description: Shows the total stats of the slot command for this bot's session.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .slottestGambling
description: Tests to see how much slots payout for X number of plays.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .slotGambling
description: Play Nadeko slots. Max bet is 9999. 1.5 second cooldown per user.

name: .waifuresetGambling
description: Resets your waifu stats, except current waifus.

name: .claimwaifuGambling
description: Claim a waifu for yourself by spending currency.  You must spend at least 10% more than her current value unless she set .affinity towards you.

name: .waifutransferGambling
description: Transfer the ownership of one of your waifus to another user. You must pay 10% of your waifu's value.

name: .divorceGambling
description: Releases your claim on a specific waifu. You will get some of the money you've spent back unless that waifu has an affinity towards you. 6 hours cooldown.

name: .affinityGambling
description: Sets your affinity towards someone you want to be claimed by. Setting affinity will reduce their .claim on you by 20%. Provide no parameters to clear your affinity. 30 minutes cooldown.

name: .waifusGambling
description: Shows top 9 waifus. You can specify another page to show other waifus.

name: .waifuinfoGambling
description: Shows waifu stats for a target person. Defaults to you if no user is provided.

name: .waifugiftGambling
description: Gift an item to someone. This will increase their waifu value by 50% of the gifted item's value if you are not their waifu, or 95% if you are. Provide no parameters to see a list of items that you can gift.

name: .wheeloffortuneGambling
description: Bets a certain amount of currency on the wheel of fortune. Wheel can stop on one of many different multipliers. Won amount is rounded down to the nearest whole number.

name: .wheeltestGambling
description: wheeltest

name: .chooseGames
description: Chooses a thing from a list of things

name: .8ballGames
description: Ask the 8ball a yes/no question.

name: .rategirlGames
description: Use the universal hot-crazy wife zone matrix to determine the girl's worth. It is everything young men need to know about women. At any moment in time, any woman you have previously located on this chart can vanish from that location and appear anywhere else on the chart.

name: .linuxGames
description: Prints a customizable Linux interjection

name: .acrophobiaGames
description: Starts an Acrophobia game. Options --submission-time (-s)   Time after which the submissions are closed and voting starts.--vote-time (-v)   Time after which the voting is closed and the winner is declared.

name: .cleverbotGames
description: Toggles cleverbot session. When enabled, the bot will reply to messages starting with bot mention in the server. Custom reactions starting with %mention% won't work if cleverbot is enabled.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .hangmanlistGames
description: Shows a list of hangman term types.

name: .hangmanGames
description: Starts a game of hangman in the channel. Use .hangmanlist to see a list of available term types. Defaults to 'all'.

name: .hangmanstopGames
description: Stops the active hangman game on this channel if it exists.

name: .leetGames
description: Converts a text to leetspeak with 6 (1-6) severity levels

name: .nunchiGames
description: Creates or joins an existing nunchi game. Users have to count up by 1 from the starting number shown by the bot. If someone makes a mistake (types an incorrect number, or repeats the same number) they are out of the game and a new round starts without them.  Minimum 3 users required.

name: .pickGames
description: Picks the currency planted in this channel. If the plant has a password, you need to specify it.

name: .plantGames
description: Spend an amount of currency to plant it in this channel. Default is 1. You can specify the password after the amount. Password has to be alphanumeric and it will be trimmed down to 10 characters if it's longer.

name: .gencurrencyGames
description: Toggles currency generation on this channel. Every posted message will have chance to spawn currency. Chance is specified by the Bot Owner. (default is 2%)RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .gencurlistGames
description: Shows the list of server and channel ids where gc is enabled. Paginated with 9 per page.RequiresManageMessages Server PermissionBot Owner Only

name: .pollGames
description: Creates a public poll which requires users to type a number of the voting option in the channel command is ran in.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .pollstatsGames
description: Shows the poll results without stopping the poll on this server.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .pollendGames
description: Stops active poll on this server and prints the results in this channel.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .typestartGames
description: Starts a typing contest. Options --start-time (-s)   How long does it take for the race to start. Default 5.

name: .typestopGames
description: Stops a typing contest on the current channel.

name: .typeaddGames
description: Adds a new article to the typing contest.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .typelistGames
description: Lists added typing articles with their IDs. 15 per page.

name: .typedelGames
description: Deletes a typing article given the ID.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .tictactoeGames
description: Starts a game of tic tac toe. Another user must run the command in the same channel in order to accept the challenge. Use numbers 1-9 to play. Options --turn-timer (-t)   Turn time in seconds. Default 15.

name: .triviaGames
description: Starts a game of trivia. You can add nohint to prevent hints. First player to get to 10 points wins by default. You can specify a different number. 30 seconds per question. Options --pokemon (-p)   Whether it's 'Who's that pokemon?' trivia.--nohint   Don't show any hints.--win-req (-w)   Winning requirement. Set 0 for an infinite game. Default 10.--question-timer (-q)   How long until the question ends. Default 30.--timeout (-t)   Number of questions of inactivity in order stop. Set 0 for never. Default 10.

name: .tlGames
description: Shows a current trivia leaderboard.

name: .tqGames
description: Quits current trivia after current question.

name: .modulesHelp
description: Lists all bot modules.

name: .commandsHelp
description: List all of the bot's commands from a certain module. You can either specify the full name or only the first few letters of the module name. Options --view (-v)   Specifies how to output the list of commands. 0 - Hide commands which you can't use, 1 - Cross out commands which you can't use, 2 - Show all.

name: .hgitHelp

name: .playMusic
description: If no parameters are specified, acts as .next 1 command. If you specify a song number, it will jump to that song. If you specify a search query, acts as a .q command

name: .queueMusic
description: Queue a song using keywords or a link. Bot will join your voice channel. You must be in a voice channel.

name: .queuenextMusic
description: Works the same as .queue command, except it enqueues the new song after the current one. You must be in a voice channel.

name: .queuesearchMusic
description: Search for top 5 youtube song result using keywords, and type the index of the song to play that song. Bot will join your voice channel. You must be in a voice channel.

name: .listqueueMusic
description: Lists 10 currently queued songs per page. Default page is 1.

name: .nextMusic
description: Goes to the next song in the queue. You have to be in the same voice channel as the bot. You can skip multiple songs, but in that case songs will not be requeued if .rcs or .rpl is enabled.

name: .stopMusic
description: Stops the music and preserves the current song index. Stays in the channel.

name: .autodisconnectMusic
description: Toggles whether the bot should disconnect from the voice channel once it's done playing all of the songs.

name: .destroyMusic
description: Completely stops the music and unbinds the bot from the channel. (may cause weird behaviour)

name: .pauseMusic
description: Pauses or Unpauses the song.

name: .volumeMusic
description: Sets the music playback volume (0-100%)

name: .defvolMusic
description: Sets the default music volume when music playback is started (0-100). Persists through restarts.

name: .songremoveMusic
description: Remove a song by its # in the queue, or 'all' to remove all songs from the queue and reset the song index.

name: .playlistsMusic
description: Lists all playlists. Paginated, 20 per page.

name: .deleteplaylistMusic
description: Deletes a saved playlist using its id. Works only if you made it or if you are the bot owner.

name: .playlistshowMusic
description: Lists all songs in a playlist spepcified by its id. Paginated, 20 per page.

name: .saveMusic
description: Saves a playlist under a certain name. Playlist name must be no longer than 20 characters and must not contain dashes.

name: .loadMusic
description: Loads a saved playlist using its ID. Use .pls to list all saved playlists and .save to save new ones.

name: .fairplayMusic
description: Toggles fairplay. While enabled, the bot will prioritize songs from users who didn't have their song recently played instead of the song's position in the queue.

name: .songautodeleteMusic
description: Toggles whether the song should be automatically removed from the music queue when it finishes playing.

name: .soundcloudqueueMusic
description: Queue a soundcloud song using keywords. Bot will join your voice channel. You must be in a voice channel.

name: .soundcloudplMusic
description: Queue a Soundcloud playlist using a link.

name: .nowplayingMusic
description: Shows the song that the bot is currently playing.

name: .shuffleMusic
description: Shuffles the current playlist.

name: .playlistMusic
description: Queues up to 500 songs from a youtube playlist specified by a link, or keywords.

name: .radioMusic
description: Queues a radio stream from a link. It can be a direct mp3 radio stream, .m3u, .pls .asx or .xspf (Usage Video: https://streamable.com/al54)

name: .localMusic
description: Queues a local file by specifying a full path.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .localplaylstMusic
description: Queues all songs from a directory.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .moveMusic
description: Moves the bot to your voice channel. (works only if music is already playing)

name: .movesongMusic
description: Moves a song from one position to another.

name: .setmaxqueueMusic
description: Sets a maximum queue size. Specify no parameters to have no limit.

name: .setmaxplaytimeMusic
description: Sets a maximum number of seconds (>14) a song can run before being skipped automatically. Set 0 to have no limit.

name: .reptcursongMusic
description: Toggles repeat of current song.

name: .rpeatplaylstMusic
description: Toggles repeat of all songs in the queue (every song that finishes is added to the end of the queue).

name: .autoplayMusic
description: Toggles autoplay - When the song is finished, automatically queue a related Youtube song. (Works only for Youtube songs and when queue is empty)

name: .setmusicchannelMusic
description: Sets the current channel as the default music output channel. This will output playing, finished, paused and removed songs to that channel instead of the channel where the first song was queued in.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .unsetmusicchannelMusic
description: Bot will output playing, finished, paused and removed songs to the channel where the first song was queued in.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

You can instead specify time of day for the message to be repeated at daily (make sure you've set your server's timezone). You can have up to 5 repeating messages on the server in total. Options --message (-m)   Message to be repeated--no-redundant (-n)   Whether the message should be reposted if the last message in the channel is this same message.--interval (-i)   How frequently the repeating message is posted, in minutes.  RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .repeatlistUtility
description: Shows currently repeating messages and their indexes.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .streamroleUtility
description: Sets a role which is monitored for streamers (FromRole), and a role to add if a user from 'FromRole' is streaming (AddRole). When a user from 'FromRole' starts streaming, they will receive an 'AddRole'. Provide no parameters to disableRequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .streamrolekwUtility
description: Sets keyword which is required in the stream's title in order for the streamrole to apply. Provide no keyword in order to reset.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .streamroleblUtility
description: Adds or removes a blacklisted user. Blacklisted users will never receive the stream role.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .streamrolewlUtility
description: Adds or removes a whitelisted user. Whitelisted users will receive the stream role even if they don't have the specified keyword in their stream title.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .convertlistUtility
description: List of the convertible dimensions and currencies.

name: .convertUtility
description: Convert quantities. Use .convertlist to see supported dimensions and currencies.

name: .verboseerrorUtility
description: Toggles whether the bot should print command errors when a command is incorrectly used.RequiresManageMessages Server Permission

name: .experienceXp
description: Shows your xp stats. Specify the user to show that user's stats instead.

name: .xplvluprewardsXp
description: Shows currently set level up rewards.

name: .xprolerewardXp
description: Sets a role reward on a specified level. Provide no role name in order to remove the role reward.RequiresManageRoles Server Permission

name: .xpcurrewardXp
description: Sets a currency reward on a specified level. Provide no amount in order to remove the reward.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .xpnotifyXp
description: Sets how the bot should notify you when you get a server or global level. You can set dm (for the bot to send a direct message), channel (to get notified in the channel you sent the last message in) or none to disable.

name: .xpexcludeXp
description: Exclude a channel, role or current server from the xp system.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .xpexclusionlistXp
description: Shows the roles and channels excluded from the XP system on this server, as well as whether the whole server is excluded.

name: .xpleaderboardXp
description: Shows current server's xp leaderboard.

name: .xpgleaderboardXp
description: Shows the global xp leaderboard.

name: .xpaddXp
description: Adds xp to a user on the server. This does not affect their global ranking. You can use negative values.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission

name: .xptempreloadXp
description: Reloads the xp template file. Xp template file allows you to customize the position and color of elements on the .xp card.RequiresBot Owner Only

name: .clubtransferXp
description: Transfers the ownership of the club to another member of the club.

name: .clubadminXp
description: Assigns (or unassigns) staff role to the member of the club. Admins can ban, kick and accept applications.

name: .clubcreateXp
description: Creates a club. You must be at least level 5 and not be in the club already.

name: .clubiconXp
description: Sets the club icon.

name: .clubinfoXp
description: Shows information about the club.

name: .clubbansXp
description: Shows the list of users who have banned from your club. Paginated. You must be club owner to use this command.

name: .clubappsXp
description: Shows the list of users who have applied to your club. Paginated. You must be club owner to use this command.

name: .clubapplyXp
description: Apply to join a club. You must meet that club's minimum level requirement, and not be on its ban list.

name: .clubacceptXp
description: Accept a user who applied to your club.

name: .clubleaveXp
description: Leaves the club you're currently in.

name: .clubkickXp
description: Kicks the user from the club. You must be the club owner. They will be able to apply again.

name: .clubbanXp
description: Bans the user from the club. You must be the club owner. They will not be able to apply again.

name: .clubunbanXp
description: Unbans the previously banned user from the club. You must be the club owner.

name: .clublevelreqXp
description: Sets the club required level to apply to join the club. You must be club owner. You can't set this number below 5.

name: .clubdescXp
description: Sets the club description. Maximum 150 characters. Club owner only.
usage: .clubdesc This is the best club please join.

name: .clubdisbandXp
description: Disbands the club you're the owner of. This action is irreversible.

name: .clublbXp
description: Shows club rankings on the specified page.

name: .xpresetXp
description: Resets specified user's XP, or the XP of all users in the server. You can't reverse this action.RequiresAdministrator Server Permission
